(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;margin: 32px 0;text-align: cen=
ter;font-weight: 500;font-style: italic;">Editor&#8217;s note: We&#8217;ve =
invited a group of writers to profile their favorite Substackers. This is t=
he first in that series.</p></div><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb=
(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">America, they say, is alread=
y dead and doesn&#8217;t know it. Whatever mystery or magic once haunted it=
s blue highways and back roads has long since fled, and anyone lighting out=
 for the territories in search of meaning and adventure will find only a gr=
im, desiccated interior; a zombieland held together by cheap entertainment,=
 political rancor, poisonous food, and despair.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 =
20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Writers, to=
o, have failed at their task. The complaint goes something like this: No lo=
nger channeling the spirit of the muddy river country that animated Twain, =
Melville, and Hemingway, our literati confine themselves to writing insular=
 dispatches from cosmopolitan enclaves, in which a familiar set of themes&#=
8212;bad dates, grad school, Manhattan bohemia, going on your phone&#8212;a=
re played in slightly different ways. It all has a feeling of enervating de=
cadence: trifles, amusements, cultural exhaustion. Any vital voice in Ameri=
can letters, should it ever appear, wouldn&#8217;t find any purchase. And a=
nyway, no one even reads.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,5=
5,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Those are common views, and=
 they&#8217;re not entirely baseless. It&#8217;s hard not to feel pessimist=
ic if you look too long at the hollowed-out interior of the country and at =
the obscene divide between wealthy and wretched in the metropoles. And it&#=
8217;s hard to feel good about the state of the written word if you don&#82=
17;t venture beyond the </span><em>New York Times</em><span> bestseller lis=
t. But I know better. I haven&#8217;t yet written it all off as unsalvageab=
le. I have hope for both the country and its literary output, in no small p=
art because I read </span><span class=3D"mention-pnpTE1 mentionStatic-liMkl=
k" data-component-name=3D"MentionStatic" style=3D"white-space: nowrap;curso=
